Nike remain committed to its partnership with Chelsea, according to reports, despite shirt sponsors Three temporarily suspending their deal with the club. The telecommunications provider requested the removal of their branding from shirts and the home ground Stamford Bridge earlier this week. This comes after sanctions by the UK government were imposed on club owner Roman Abramovich. Ex-Zambian President, Banda Dies Of Cancer At 85 Gowon Flags Off Construction Of British-American Junction… But The Athletic are reporting that Nike, who have been the Blues’ kit supplier since 2016, are set to stick with the club. The sports brand are said to have signed a deal worth around £900million over 15 years with the West Londoners. Nike produces Chelsea’s match kits, replica kits, and training gear. And that is reportedly set to continue, despite the situation currently surrounding the club. Abramovich publicly put the club up for sale earlier this month, but a deal is yet to be concluded.